[2026-03-18T11:30:37.441Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01SvGsSYpHSR6fbbrmG1YQq7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01LsoWDVQvhe8KtXTHmQhCLy","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/ideas \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"scan_id\": \"c7195383-d4af-459b-9ca4-602fc28de84d\",\n    \"project_id\": \"c6fd0474-19f1-4223-b6a9-752077c51d3d\",\n    \"context_id\": \"ctx_1773782598946_lkdm50i\",\n    \"scan_type\": \"moonshot_architect\",\n    \"category\": \"functionality\",\n    \"title\": \"Speculative sandbox pre-warming from trigger patterns\",\n    \"description\": \"Implement a prediction engine that analyzes trigger history (cron schedules, event patterns, persona_action chains) to anticipate upcoming executions and pre-warm sandboxes before assignments arrive. Pre-warming includes creating the sandbox directory tree (sandbox.ts createSandboxDir), starting the network filter proxy (networkProxy.ts), and writing credential files (credentialInjector.ts) — all of which currently happen synchronously on the hot path. The orchestrator sends a hint message with predicted persona configs; workers maintain a small pool of warm sandboxes ready for instant assignment. First sprint: add a pre-warm WebSocket message type and implement a 1-slot warm sandbox cache in the worker that pre-creates the sandbox dir and env for the most recently executed persona.\",\n    \"reasoning\": \"Cold-start latency for sandbox setup (mkdir, credential write, proxy start, bwrap spawn) adds hundreds of milliseconds to every execution. For scheduled personas that fire predictably, this latency is entirely avoidable. Pre-warming transforms perceived execution speed from good to instant, which is the difference between a tool and a magical experience.\",\n    \"effort\": 7,\n    \"impact\": 7,\n    \"risk\": 5\n  }'","description":"Save idea 2: Sp